INSERT INTO `sections` (`templateId`, `name`, `introduction`, `requirements`, `guidance`, `displayOrder`, `isDirty`, `createdById`, `created`, `modifiedById`, `modified`) (SELECT `templates`.`id`, 'Long-term archiving and preservation details', 'Auraria Institutional Repository (AIR) may be used to preserve, publish and archive your data.&nbsp; The materials in AIR will be stored, preserved, and made accessible at no cost to the project and long-term maintenance of these materials will become the Auraria Library&rsquo;s responsibility upon ingest. While it is difficult to guarantee set periods of time, Auraria Library strives to ensure preservation of digital materials during the life of the Library. The Auraria Institutional Repository provides an exceptionally high-quality environment for digital discovery, accessibility, transmissibility, and preservation. The Auraria Library faculty and staff are experts in operating, managing, and sustaining digital objects in repositories, possessing experience with multiple metadata schemes, metadata harvesting, and crawling of digital objects, digital rights management, and preservation.<br /><br />Contact: <a href="mailto:matthew.mariner@ucdenver.edu">matthew.mariner@ucdenver.edu</a><br /><br />The following are examples of wording that may be included in in the data mangement plan relating to AIR.<br /><br />1. These data elements will be maintained for the required minimum of 3 years and up to the life of the Auraria Library. In the event the PI, <strong><em>name</em></strong>, leaves the University of Colorado Denver prior to this time the data will be moved to the relocating institution, and/or the original institution will maintain the data or the required duration. The expected volume of data should not exceed <strong><em>20~TB</em></strong>, thus the cost of keeping the data is expected to be marginal. <br /><br />2. The PI will utilize the Auraria Institutional Repository (AIR) at the University of Colorado Denver (http://digital.auraria.edu/air). AIR is a digital library of intellectual output of the Auraria Campus community and serves as a central location for the secure storage, collection, and free dissemination of campus-produced open-access creative works and historical materials related to the campus community. When new versions of <strong><em>our software</em></strong> are released, the PI, <em><strong>name</strong></em>, will archive these in AIR to provide a permanent linkable DOI. The software developed under this project will be available for dissemination and commercialization of enhanced or customized versions, or for incorporation into other software packages. The source code for all developed software will be available and will include the ability of researchers to modify the source code and to share modifications with colleagues. As noted above, release versions of the software will be maintained by the PI. Improvements to the software by other developers within the larger research community will be maintained in software branches through version control software such as GitHub, and eventually merged into the main release version as the software matures and has undergone extensive testing. <br /><br />3. The Auraria Institutional Repository (AIR) is an open access digital library and service provided, operated, and managed by the Auraria Library. For all digital materials submitted to AIR, the Library offers secure storage of digital files; stable and permanent URLs; redundant backup of digital materials in off-site locations, usage statistics (e-mailed monthly to contributors), and indexing in major search engines. AIR utilizes OAI-PMH (Open Archives Initiative &ndash;Protocol for Metadata Harvesting) to aggregate all digital objects in our library discovery tool, Summon, and may also use it to distribute those objects via other platforms (e.g., Digital Public Library of America).  <p>AIR will assign a Creative Commons CC-BY license to all materials uploaded to AIR. This license lets others distribute, remix, tweak, and build upon the work, even commercially, as long as they credit us for the original creation. This is the most accommodating of licenses and enables maximum dissemination and use of the materials.<br /><br /><br /></p>', '', '', 2, 0, `templates`.`createdById`, `templates`.`created`, `templates`.`modifiedById`, `templates`.`modified` FROM `templates` WHERE `ownerId` = 'https://ror.org/02hh7en24' AND `name` = 'Auraria Institutional Repository role in your Data Management Plan');
