INSERT INTO `sections` (`templateId`, `name`, `introduction`, `requirements`, `guidance`, `displayOrder`, `isDirty`, `createdById`, `created`, `modifiedById`, `modified`) (SELECT `templates`.`id`, 'Data Sharing', '<p>All personnel with access to the controlled technology and their nationality must be listed in this section. Project Director or lead PI will notify ORC if personnel need to be added to this TCP or be removed. All personnel assigned to this project and all visitors that will be given access to potentially EAR-controlled data, including visual access, will be screened against U.S. Government denied parties lists prior to being given such access. <strong>Any changes to the personnel having access to controlled information covered under this TCP must be cleared in advance by the Office of Research Integrity and Outreach.</strong><br /><br />&nbsp;All shipments containing information or items controlled under this TCP must be reviewed with the Office of Research Integrity and Outreach. Please, send the Shipping Information Form to RIO to request approval for the shipment.&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>  <p>If applicable for this project, the procurement of EAR parts, tooling and equipment specifically designed, developed, configured, adapted, or modified for use with an EAR-controlled item must be purchased from suppliers and vendors who can certify the suppliers/vendors are EAR-compliant. Procurement must be coordinated with the Office of Research Compliance and Procurement Management.</p>  <p class="MsoNormal"><strong>Note from the Export Controls Team: </strong>You will receive a statement from the Export Control team concerning the jurisdiction and classification of the information, software, or items controlled by this TCP, and the controls and restrictions required by that classification. Please include this statement in the field below concerning the restrictions on release or dissemination of the data.&nbsp;</p>', 