INSERT INTO `sections` (`templateId`, `name`, `introduction`, `requirements`, `guidance`, `displayOrder`, `isDirty`, `createdById`, `created`, `modifiedById`, `modified`) (SELECT `templates`.`id`, 'Data Repositories', '<p>In an effort to promote open-science principles of transparency and reproducibility, funding agencies and journals increasingly require depositing data in a repository upon publication or conclusion of a study. In many cases, journals have specific requirements regarding what repository to use for long-term storage that should also be considered.</p>  <p>Below are public repositories recommended by high-impact scientific journals for specific data types, as well as generalist and code repositories. Please use this as a starting point for targeting what repositories to use. For each study data type, select repositories to target for data publication.</p>  <p>For researchers conducting NIH-supported research, the NIH provides <a href="https://grants.nih.gov/grants/guide/notice-files/NOT-OD-21-016.html">additional guidance</a> on selecting a data repository. Non NIH-specific guidance is provided by sources including the&nbsp;<a href="https://www.f1000.com/researcher_blog/how-to-choose-a-repository/">Faculty of 1000</a>, and the <a href="https://www.dcc.ac.uk/guidance/how-guides/where-keep-research-data">Digital Curation Center</a>. <a href="https://fairsharing.org/search?fairsharingRegistry=Database">FAIRsharing</a> and the <a href="http://www.re3data.org/">Registry of Research Data Repositories</a> provide searchable collections of repositories.</p>', '', '', 8, 0, `templates`.`createdById`, `templates`.`created`, `templates`.`modifiedById`, `templates`.`modified` FROM `templates` WHERE `ownerId` = 'https://ror.org/03e62d071' AND `name` = 'Knight Cancer Institute DMP Outline Tool');
